items.name: Capacidade Restante - Battery Group
items.description: Total Remaining Capacity Percent. Value range: 0 to 100, units: %, and the value is an integer.(1). If the value is 2147483647(0x7FFFFFFF), it indicates that the value is invalid.

triggers.name: Retificadora - Capacidade restante da Bateria em {ITEM.LASTVALUE}

items.name: Charge Status - Battery Group
items.description:
"Battery charging state, indicates the charging and discharging information about the battery group.
 
1, it indicates a battery group in the float charging state.
2, it indicates a battery group in the boost charging state.
3, it indicates a battery group in the discharging state.
4, it indicates a battery group in the hibernating state.
7, it indicates a battery group in the Offline state.

triggers.recovery_expression:
last(/Huawei Retificadora ETP4860 by SNMP - Sintercom/rectifier.battery.group[chargeStatus.0])=2

or

last(/Huawei Retificadora ETP4860 by SNMP - Sintercom/rectifier.battery.group[chargeStatus.0])=1
triggers.name: Retificadora - Sem energia elétrica (Modo Bateria)
triggers.description:
1, it indicates a battery group in the float charging state.
2, it indicates a battery group in the boost charging state.
3, it indicates a battery group in the discharging state.
4, it indicates a battery group in the hibernating state.
7, it indicates a battery group in the Offline state.

items.name: Tempo de Descarregamento - Battery Group
items.description: Battery group backup time. It indicates the real-time statistics of the battery group. Value range: 0 to 15360, Units: minutes (min), and the value is an integer (1). If the value is 2147483647(0x7FFFFFFF), it indicates that the value is invalid.

triggers.name: Retificadora - Tempo restante da Bateria em {ITEM.LASTVALUE}

items.name: Rated Voltage - Modules Group
items.description: Rated voltage of the rectifier module group. It is an inherent attribute. Value range: 42 to 58.3, Units: V, and the value is accurate to one decimal place (.1). If the value is 2147483647(0x7FFFFFFF), it indicates that the value is invalid.

items.name: Total AC Input Power - Modules Group
items.description: Total power of the direct current output. Value range: 0 to 100000000, units: W, and the value is an integer. If the value is 2147483647(0x7FFFFFFF), it indicates that the value is invalid.

items.name: Total DC Power - Modules Group
items.description: Total power of the direct current output. Value range: 0 to 100000000, units: W, and the value is an integer. If the value is 2147483647(0x7FFFFFFF), it indicates that the value is invalid.

items.name: Status - Modules Group
items.description: "Power-on or power-off of the rectifier module group (all the rectifier modules) on the site. It is an enumeration value: If the NMS notifies the SNMP agent that this node is set to 1, it indicates power-on of all rectifier modules; If the NMS notifies the SNMP agent that this node is set to 2, it indicates power-off of all the rectifier modules; If the NMS notifies the SNMP agent that this node is set to 255, it indicates nullOper of all the rectifier modules. NOTE: Only the system in manual mode, this parameter can be configured successfully."

items.name: Quantity Modules in Group
items.description: Total quantity of the rectifier modules. Value range: 0 to 256. Units:pcs.

items.name: Rectifier Status - 28672

triggers.expression: last(/Huawei Retificadora ETP4860 by SNMP - Sintercom/rectifier.status[28672])>=2
triggers.name: Retificadora - Módulo 28672 Indisponível ou Instável

items.name: Rectifier Status - 28673

triggers.expression: last(/Huawei Retificadora ETP4860 by SNMP - Sintercom/rectifier.status[28673])>=2
triggers.name: Retificadora - Módulo 28673 Indisponível ou Instável

items.name: Load Usage
items.description: Load Usage. Value range: 0 to 150, units: %, and the value is an integer. If the value is 2147483647(0x7FFFFFFF), it indicates that the value is invalid.

items.name: Rectifier Temperature - 28672
items.description: Rectifier Temperature. Value range: -300 to 300, units: degC, and the value is accurate to one decimal space (.1). If the value is 2147483647(0x7FFFFFFF), it indicates that the value is invalid.

items.name: Rectifier Temperature - 28673
items.description: Rectifier Temperature. Value range: -300 to 300, units: degC, and the value is accurate to one decimal space (.1). If the value is 2147483647(0x7FFFFFFF), it indicates that the value is invalid.

items.name: System contact details
items.description:
MIB: SNMPv2-MIB
The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person.  If no contact information is known, the value is the zero-length string.

items.name: System description
items.description:
MIB: SNMPv2-MIB
A textual description of the entity. This value should
include the full name and version identification of the system's hardware type, software operating-system, and
networking software.

items.name: System location
items.description:
MIB: SNMPv2-MIB
The physical location of this node (e.g., `telephone closet, 3rd floor').  If the location is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

items.name: System name
items.description:
MIB: SNMPv2-MIB
An administratively-assigned name for this managed node.By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name.  If the name is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

items.name: Uptime (network)
items.description:
MIB: SNMPv2-MIB
The time (in hundredths of a second) since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized.

items.name: System object ID
items.description:
MIB: SNMPv2-MIB
The vendor's authoritative identification of the network management subsystem contained in the entity.  This value is allocated within the SMI enterprises subtree (1.3.6.1.4.1) and provides an easy and unambiguous means for determining`what kind of box' is being managed.  For example, if vendor`Flintstones, Inc.' was assigned the subtree1.3.6.1.4.1.4242, it could assign the identifier 1.3.6.1.4.1.4242.1.1 to its `Fred Router'.

items.name: SNMP agent availability
items.description:
Availability of SNMP checks on the host. The value of this item corresponds to availability icons in the host list.
Possible value:
0 - not available
1 - available
2 - unknown
